So close, yet so far...

https://github.com/dotnet/corefx/blob/master/src/System.Net.WebSockets.Client/src/System/Net/WebSockets/WebSocketHandle.Unix.cs

@Tratcher do you know whether support on linux will be coming? It's super sad to see a netstandard lib that's not netstandard :(

Here is code for a client:

```
_client = new WebSocketClient {
                ConfigureRequest = (req) => {
                    var header = new AuthenticationHeaderValue("Bearer", _accessToken);
                    req.Headers.Add("Authorization", header.ToString());
                }
            };
```

And for the server inside Configure method:

```
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer;
...

            var jwtOptions = new JwtBearerOptions {
                AuthenticationScheme = JwtBearerDefaults.AuthenticationScheme,
                Authority = "https://example.com/id/",
                Audience = "https://example.com",
                AutomaticAuthenticate = true,
                RequireHttpsMetadata = false
            };
            jwtOptions.ConfigurationManager = new ConfigurationManager<OpenIdConnectConfiguration>
                (
                    metadataAddress: jwtOptions.Authority + ".well-known/openid-configuration",
                    configRetriever: new OpenIdConnectConfigurationRetriever(),
                    docRetriever: new HttpDocumentRetriever { RequireHttps = true }
                );
            app.UseJwtBearerAuthentication(jwtOptions);
```

After that `context.User.Identity` is authenticated, claims collection is populated and I could apply any logic before accepting WebSockets.

This works inside ASP.NET Core Kestrel server using .NET 451 with a standalone remote IdentityServer3.

